  "doc_id": "52066",
  "text": "Normal murine ASL composition. The values for the ions detected in murine ASL and plasma are shown in Table 1 . Although results in plasma were as expected, the major ionic species Na ϩ and Cl Ϫ were significantly lower in ASL than they were in plasma. This finding is consistent with previous reports of low ASL salinity in other species, including measurements from the rat collected in vivo (10) and the horse collected in vitro [CITATION_1] . Perhaps more importantly, ASL collected from human subjects has been reported repeatedly to have lower Na ϩ and Cl Ϫ levels than those in plasma [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In all of these reports (except Ref. 14, which reports only Cl Ϫ values), the Na ϩ from normal ASL was reported to be between 80 and 85 mM. Therefore, our finding of 87.2 Ϯ 3.0 mM Na ϩ is in agreement with previous reports. We did, however, find a considerably lower Cl Ϫ value than has been reported by others (57.0 Ϯ 3.0 mM vs. a range of 84-108 mM) [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] , with the presence of a considerable anion gap (30 mM). Additionally, we found considerably lower values for K ϩ in ASL than previously reported (4.7 Ϯ 0.4 vs. 20-29 mM), with approximately equivalent values between ASL and plasma. Given that osmolarity is often determined from two times Na ϩ and K ϩ concentration, the apparent osmolarity of this liquid was 183 mosM compared with ϳ250 mosM for plasma. However, it is important to note that we were not able to directly measure osmolarity. We additionally report values for HCO [CITATION_10] Ϫ and PO 4 3Ϫ to be lower in mouse ASL than in plasma, while SO 4 2Ϫ levels are higher. Ionic composition of ASL from B6-Cftr UNCϪ/Ϫ and B6-Cftr UNCϩ/ϩ mice. ASL from CF patients has been reported to exhibit either elevated salinity [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] or identical levels of Na ϩ or Cl Ϫ compared with normal subjects [CITATION_13] [CITATION_14] . To evaluate the contribution of functional CFTR Cl Ϫ channels to ASL composition, we attempted to collect ASL from a knockout mouse strain raised on a C57BL/6 background in which the gene encoding the CFTR protein has been disrupted. Although we successfully sampled ASL from four of eight B6-Cftr UNCϪ/Ϫ mice (a similar success rate to normal C57BL/6 mice), we were only able to collect a sufficient quantity of ASL for reproducible CE analysis from two of these mice. Results were similar between B6-Cftr UNCϪ/Ϫ mice (Na ϩ , 84.8 Ϯ 5.7 mM; K ϩ , 4.8 Ϯ 0.01 mM; Cl Ϫ , 49.1 Ϯ 18.9 mM; HCO 3 Ϫ , 4.8 Ϯ 1.6 mM) and their littermate B6-Cftr UNCϩ/ϩ controls (Na ϩ , 85.6 Ϯ 15.8 mM; K ϩ , 5.2 Ϯ 1.1 mM; Cl Ϫ , 66.2 Ϯ 7.8 mM; HCO 3 Ϫ , 5.1 Ϯ 0.7 mM).",
